class Solution {
    public int[] maxDepthAfterSplit(String seq) {
        int[] answer = new int[seq.length()];
        int depth = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < seq.length(); i++) {
            char c = seq.charAt(i);
            if (c == '(') {
                depth++;
                answer[i] = depth & 1;
            } else {
                answer[i] = depth & 1;
                depth--;
            }
        }
        return answer;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the input string once, maintaining a depth counter. It assigns each character to either subsequence A or B based on the current depth, ensuring that the maximum depth of A and B is minimized. The use of bitwise AND (&) with 1 effectively alternates between 0 and 1 for consecutive odd or even depths.
